Sentencas: Ni-Fe alloy supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were successfully fabricated by a low cost and simple process involving phase-inversion, co-sintering and in situ reduction.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction

Sentencas: The tubular metal supports have a special structure consisting of uniformly distributed sponge-like pores.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction

Sentencas: It has proven that co-sintering the as-prepared tubular supports together with half cells (anode and electrolyte layers) is in favor of obtaining the YSZ crack free electrolyte film.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction

Sentencas: In addition to the support for SOFC, the Ni-Fe alloy tube also serves as current collector at the anode side after fully in situ reduction.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the Ni-Fe alloy supported tubular SOFCs are 0.26 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, using moist hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction

Sentencas: The present work demonstrates the feasibility for the fabrication of metal-supported SOFCs with acceptable performance using economical techniques.
Titulo: Fabrication of metal-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cell by phase-inversion method and in situ reduction
